{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599277","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599277"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:51:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15536"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15536","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15536"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.15,0,0.65,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8227"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114273"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8227","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8227"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15536"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96273"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"6694"},{"type":"tags","id":"7010"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19894"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19897"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22665"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114273"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adrenal (suprarenal) glands are paired endocrine organs located superior to each kidney. They receive rich arterial supply and have distinct venous drainage patterns. There is single venous drainage from the hilum of each adrenal gland.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following correctly describes the venous drainage pattern?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inferior vena cava bilaterally","Inferior vena cava on left and renal vein on right","Renal veins bilaterally","Renal vein on left and inferior vena cava on right","Superior mesenteric vein bilaterally"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe venous drainage of the adrenal glands follows an asymmetric pattern. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle vein from hilum drains to renal vein on left and inferior vena cava on right\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle vein from hilum drains to renal veins bilaterally\u003C/strong\u003E does not account for the right side draining to the inferior vena cava. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle vein from hilum drains to inferior vena cava bilaterally\u003C/strong\u003E fails to recognise that the left side drains to the left renal vein. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle vein from hilum drains to inferior vena cava on left and renal vein on right\u003C/strong\u003E represents the opposite of the correct pattern. The \u003Cstrong\u003Esingle vein from hilum drains to superior mesenteric vein bilaterally\u003C/strong\u003E would place the adrenal veins in the portal system, which does not occur.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The right suprarenal vein drains directly into the inferior vena cava","The left suprarenal vein drains into the left renal vein"],"references":["Lotfi CFP, Kremer JL, Dos Santos Passaia B, Cavalcante IP. The human adrenal cortex: growth control and disorders. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2018 Sep 6;73(suppl 1):e473s. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2018/e473s. PMID: 30208164; PMCID: PMC6113920","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96273"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15536"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96273"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-15T14:35:29+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-15T14:35:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8227"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114273"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4929"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6d","name":"Endocrine","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50: